  :topic: Chapter8/getting_user_input
  :from_source: T
  :language: cpp

  The active code below is an example of what getting input from the
  user might look like using ``getline``.
  ~~~~
  #include <iostream>
  #include <string>
  using namespace std;

  int main () {
     string name;

     cout << "What is your full name? ";
     getline (cin, name);
     cout << "Hello " << name << "!" << endl;
  }